pouch: the AF_UNIX bulk-ring hint -- SO_SNDBUF/SO_RCVBUF -> DMSRVBULK (CF-3 B)

Maps the POSIX socket-buffer hint onto the Thylacine per-service ring
class (CONCURRENT-FS.md CF-3 B). A pre-bind setsockopt(SOL_SOCKET,
SO_SNDBUF or SO_RCVBUF, >= 128 KiB) on an AF_UNIX socket marks the slot
BULK; bind()'s create=post then carries the DMSRVBULK perm bit, so every
connection minted on the service gets 128 KiB-frame rings and a
kernel-attached mount negotiates a 128 KiB msize. stratumd's listener
setup (stm_stratumd_listen_unix, the thylacine-pouch-arm branch) is the
consumer -- on a Linux/macOS host build the same setsockopt is just a
real (advisory) buffer-size request, so the stratumd code needs no
platform gate.

Three files, stacking on 0006 (the AF_UNIX socket layer) + 0016 (the
setsockopt override):
  - src/internal/_pouch_socket.h  POUCH_SRV_DMSRVBULK + POUCH_SRV_BULK_MIN
                                  + the per-slot bulk_hint field.
  - src/network/setsockopt.c     the FAM_UNIX SO_SNDBUF/SO_RCVBUF arm
                                  (accept-any as advisory; >= the
                                  threshold sets the hint; every other
                                  AF_UNIX option stays ENOPROTOOPT).
  - src/network/bind.c           OR the hint into the walk_create perm.
--- a/src/internal/_pouch_socket.h
+++ b/src/internal/_pouch_socket.h
@@ -74,6 +74,14 @@
